tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ar_user_interactions (
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    engagement_score INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, interaction_timestamp)
)

CREATE TABLE ar_metrics (
    interaction_id INT,
    app_id INT,
    ar_experience VARCHAR(100),
    metric_type VARCHAR(50),
    metric_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE app_session (
    session_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    session_start TIMESTAMP,
    session_end TIMESTAMP,
    session_duration INT
);

CREATE TABLE sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    session_start TIMESTAMP,
    session_end TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE app_interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES sessions(session_id)
);

CREATE TABLE engagement_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    interaction_id INT,
    engagement_score INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES sessions(session_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (interaction_id) REFERENCES app_interactions(interaction_id)
);

CREATE TABLE app_errors (
    error_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    error_description TEXT,
    error_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES sessions(session_id)
);
